 make the executive profile a little bit shorter. This is still too long, so just tell me on each page what line to cut out. Using Tool | Summarize Large Document Give me the complete verbatim text of every section of this resume page by page - every single line, bullet point, and sentence exactly as written. I need to see every word on every page. View Using Tool | Think Now I have the full verbatim content. The user has several specific requests: 1. They added bullet points to v4 — good 2. They clarified that they did NOT personally work hands-on with defined benefit plans — they want accurate language that's \"adjacent\" not claiming direct DB/DC operations experience 3. They sat as a board member for Jamaica YMCA, Jamaica Queens, NY — this should be added (civil service/governance type role) 4. The executive profile is too long — they want to know what specific lines to cut on each page 5. The \"Defined Benefit and DC Pension Operations\" language in Core Competencies is a stretch — needs to be softened Let me go through page by page and identify exactly what to cut: **EXECUTIVE PROFILE (Page 1) - Issues:** Current text: \"Strategic executive partner and chief of staff professional with 25+ years across institutional finance, public sector governance, and mission-driven organizations. Recognized for translating complex financial, regulatory, and policy information into clear, high-impact executive communications. Columbia MBA (Robert Toigo Fellow). Two-time Governor Appointee. White House Fellow. Direct experience combining institutional finance fluency and executive writing capability to every leadership role.\" The last sentence \"Direct experience combining institutional finance fluency and executive writing capability to every leadership role\" is redundant and awkward. CUT IT. Also the profile could be tightened to 2-3 sentences. **Issues with accuracy:** - Core Competencies: \"Defined Benefit & DC Pension Operations\" - this needs to be changed to something like \"Pension Fund Operations Context\" or \"Pension-Adjacent Financial Services\" or removed entirely - MA in Demography description: \"the academic discipline underlying defined benefit pension fund actuarial science\" — this is fine, it's framing her education not claiming she did DB operations **Jamaica YMCA Board Member:** This needs to be added. It should go either: - Under Government Appointments & Public Service section (most appropriate - board governance) - Or as a separate \"Board Service & Community Leadership\" section - Given it's civic/community board service, it fits best in the Government Appointments section or as its own subsection **Page by page cuts:** PAGE 1: - Executive Profile: CUT the last sentence \"Direct experience combining institutional finance fluency and executive writing capability to every leadership role.\" — it's redundant after sentence 2 - Funded First: \"Designed and Generated $40M+\" — the word \"Designed and\" doesn't make sense before \"Generated.\" Should be just \"Generated $40M+...\" - Carver Bank entry is missing the date range (2015-2023) — should add that - The bullets in Government Appointments section have mixed formatting — some use \"●\" and some use \"-\" PAGE 2: - NY Life: The Innovation Group bullet \"Supported development of HECM (Home Equity Conversion Mortgage) investment vehicles, and cash flow projections — into executive-level stakeholder materials for strategy and regulatory compliance requirements.\" — this sentence is incomplete/confusing. It starts with \"cash flow projections\" but doesn't complete the thought properly. - Towers Perrin: \"Applied Masters in Demography from the University of Pennsylvania and the East West Center at the University of Hawaii to population-based mortality modeling and for employee benefits and retirement plans.\" — \"and the East West Center at the University of Hawaii\" is odd — the East West Center is typically a research institution in Hawaii, not part of UPenn. This needs clarification. If she did some coursework there, fine, but it's confusing. PAGE 3: - MA Demography: \"the academic discipline underlying defined benefit pension fund actuarial science\" — this is fine as framing, not a direct claim - Core Competencies: REMOVE \"Defined Benefit & DC Pension Operations\" since she confirmed she didn't do this. Replace with \"Pension-Adjacent Financial Services\" or \"Investment Management Context\" (which is already there) - Actually looking at the Core Competencies in v4 it says: \"Financial Services Fluency · Investment Management Context · Actuarial Framework Understanding\" — this is already softened language. The \"Defined Benefit & DC Pension Operations\" was in our v6 Google Doc but may not be in this v4. Let me recheck... The v4 Core Competencies says: \"Executive Communications & Briefing Writing · Chief of Staff Operations · Strategic Writing & Correspondence · Stakeholder Liaison & Relationship Management · Project Management & Executive Coordination · Policy Advisory · Fiduciary Standards & Compliance · Financial Services Fluency · Investment Management Context · Actuarial Framework Understanding · Lending Strategy & Credit Policy · Cross-Departmental Alignment · Microsoft Office Suite & Productivity Tools\" — OK so the v4 already uses \"Investment Management Context\" and \"Actuarial Framework Understanding\" — that's good, those are softer/accurate terms. So the main issues to fix per the user's specific requests are: 1. EXECUTIVE PROFILE: CUT last sentence 2. Add Jamaica YMCA Board membership 3. Fix Carver Bank missing dates 4. Fix the incomplete NY Life HECM bullet 5. Fix \"Designed and Generated\" Funded First bullet 6. Soften/remove any DB/DC pension operations claims (mostly already done in v4) Let me now format the response as the user requested: \"tell me on each page what line to cut out\" This should be a very tactical, line-by-line response. View Good. Full content read. Here is your line-by-line surgical edit guide — page by page, exactly what to cut, what to fix, and what to add. Nothing vague. ✂️ v4 EDIT GUIDE — Line by Line, Page by Page 3 things driving all edits: You didn't personally operate DB/DC pension plans — fix the language Jamaica YMCA Board membership needs to be added Executive Profile is too long — cut one sentence 📄 PAGE 1 — 3 Cuts, 1 Fix, 1 Add ✂️ CUT #1 — Executive Profile (Last Sentence) Text DELETE this entire sentence:\t\"Direct experience combining institutional finance fluency and executive writing capability to every leadership role.\" Why:\tIt repeats sentence 2 verbatim in different words. Sentence 2 already says it better. Cutting this tightens the profile to 3 clean sentences. After cut, profile ends at:\t\"…White House Fellow.\" — clean and punchy. ✂️ CUT #2 — Funded First, Bullet 2 (Word Fix) Text Current:\t\"Designed and Generated $40M+ in client revenue…\" DELETE:\tThe word \"Designed and\" Keep as:\t\"Generated $40M+ in client revenue; Keynote speaker on entrepreneurship…\" Why:\t\"Designed and Generated\" doesn't parse correctly. Generated is the verb. Also lowercase the K in \"Keynote\" → \"keynote speaker\" ➕ ADD — Jamaica YMCA Board Membership Where to insert: At the bottom of the GOVERNMENT APPOINTMENTS & PUBLIC SERVICE section, after the White House Fellowship entry. Copy Board Member — Jamaica YMCA  |  Jamaica, Queens, NY  |  [Year–Year] • Served as volunteer board member for community-serving nonprofit organization • Contributed governance oversight, strategic input, and community development perspective • Engaged with organizational leadership on program delivery, fiscal stewardship, and community impact strategy ✏️ Fill in the years — what years did you serve on the YMCA board? 🔧 FIX — Carver Bank Missing Date Text Current:\tConsultant to Chief Lending Officer | Carver Federal Savings Bank | New York, NY — no date Add:\t` Why:\tEvery other role has a date. Missing dates on consulting roles look like gaps. 📄 PAGE 2 — 2 Cuts, 1 Fix ✂️ CUT #3 — NY Life HECM Bullet (Broken Sentence) Text Current (broken):\t\"Supported development of HECM (Home Equity Conversion Mortgage) investment vehicles, and cash flow projections — into executive-level stakeholder materials for strategy and regulatory compliance requirements.\" Problem:\tThe sentence breaks mid-thought. It starts with \"cash flow projections\" but has no verb connecting to \"into executive-level materials.\" Replace with this clean version:\t\"Translated complex actuarial, regulatory, and financial frameworks — including HECM reverse mortgage product development — into executive-level presentations and board-ready materials for senior leadership and regulatory audiences.\" Why this works:\tAccurately says you translated the complexity into communications — which is exactly what you did. No claim you built or operated the product. ✂️ CUT #4 — Towers Perrin, Confusing University Reference Text Current:\t\"Applied Masters in Demography from the University of Pennsylvania and the East West Center at the University of Hawaii to population-based mortality modeling…\" DELETE:\t\"and the East West Center at the University of Hawaii\" Keep as:\t\"Applied MA in Demography (University of Pennsylvania) to population-based mortality modeling for employee benefits and retirement plan projections.\" Why:\tThe East West Center reference confuses the reader — it looks like you have two degrees. If it was a fellowship or program, it belongs in a separate line or footnote, not mid-sentence. Does it need to stay? 🔧 FIX — Citigroup Division Name Text Current:\t\"Management Associate, Community Investment Group | Citigroup\" Change to:\t\"Management Associate, Commercial Business Group | Citigroup\" Why:\t\"Commercial\" signals institutional finance to TRS. \"Community\" reads as community development/nonprofit. Your bullets describe commercial real estate lending — the title should match. 📄 PAGE 3 — 2 Fixes, No Cuts Needed 🔧 FIX — Core Competencies (DB/DC Language) Good news: Your v4 already uses softer, accurate language — \"Investment Management Context\" and \"Actuarial Framework Understanding.\" That's correct. Do NOT add \"Defined Benefit & DC Pension Operations\" — you confirmed you didn't operate those plans directly. One addition to make: Add \"Board Governance & Nonprofit Oversight\" to the list to reflect your Jamaica YMCA board role. Current Last 3 Competencies\tReplace/Add Investment Management Context\t✅ Keep Actuarial Framework Understanding\t✅ Keep Lending Strategy & Credit Policy\t✅ Keep (missing)\t➕ Add: Board Governance & Nonprofit Oversight 🔧 FIX — MA in Demography Bullet (Soften the DB Claim) Text Current:\t\"…the academic discipline underlying defined benefit pension fund actuarial science.\" This is fine as written — it's describing your education, not claiming you operated pension plans. It's technically accurate that demography underlies actuarial science. Keep it.\t✅ No change needed SUMMARY TABLE — All Edits at a Glance Page\tAction\tType\tWhat 1\tExecutive Profile\t✂️ CUT\tDelete last sentence starting \"Direct experience…\" 1\tFunded First bullet 2\t🔧 FIX\tDelete \"Designed and\" → lowercase \"keynote\" 1\tCarver Bank\t➕ ADD\t| 2015–2023 after New York, NY 1\tGov Appointments (bottom)\t➕ ADD\tJamaica YMCA Board Member entry (fill in years) 2\tNY Life HECM bullet\t🔧 FIX\tReplace broken sentence with clean HECM comms version 2\tTowers Perrin bullet\t✂️ CUT\tDelete \"and the East West Center at the University of Hawaii\" 2\tCitigroup title\t🔧 FIX\tChange \"Community\" to \"Commercial\" Investment Group 3\tCore Competencies\t➕ ADD\tAdd Board Governance & Nonprofit Oversight 3\tCore Competencies\t🚫 DO NOT ADD\tDo NOT add \"Defined Benefit & DC Pension Operations\" Two quick questions before I update v6 in Google Docs: Jamaica YMCA — what years did you serve on the board? (e.g., 2005–2010) East West Center — was that a fellowship, a program, or a separate academic affiliation? Do you want it kept anywhere or fully removed? Once you answer those two, I'll push all edits into the v6 Google Doc in one shot and the resume will be submission-ready. Rashida Mendes — TRS Resume FINAL v4 (Strategic Chief of Staff) (2).pdf 125.90 KB check this version Using Tool | Summarize Large Document Give me the complete verbatim text of every section, every line, every bullet point on every page of this resume exactly as written, page by page including all dates, company names, titles, and bullet content. View Using Tool | Think Now I have the full v4 (version 2) content. Let me do a thorough audit comparing it to the previous version and flag all issues: **POSITIVE CHANGES from previous version:** 1. ✅ Executive Profile - last redundant sentence is GONE - now ends at \"White House Fellow.\" Perfect. 2. ✅ Jamaica YMCA Board Member added - with date 2010 3. ✅ Funded First - \"Designed and Generated\" fixed to just \"Generated\" 4. ✅ Carver Bank - has date now (2011 - though I thought it should be 2015-2023) 5. ✅ NY Life HECM bullet fixed - now reads clearly 6. ✅ East West Center reference is still there but moved to a \"fellowship\" framing 7. ✅ Citigroup still says \"Community Business Group\" not \"Commercial\" - still needs fixing **NEW ISSUES FOUND:** 1. **NY Life dates changed to 2011-2013** - WRONG. In previous versions it was 2006-2007. Now it says 2011-2013. This is a major error - the dates don't match what was established earlier in our conversation as 2006-2007. Need to flag this. 2. **NEW ROLE APPEARED: \"VP, Relationships Management, Bank of America Commercial Lending\"** - This is a new entry that wasn't in previous versions! It says \"Prepared credit analysis, risk assessment, and deal communications across a $700 million real estate portfolio. 2006-2008\" - But it's very poorly formatted (no line break between company name and description), and the dates 2006-2008 overlap with what was previously NY Life 2006-2007. This needs clarification. Was she at BofA? If so this is a real role that needs proper formatting and accurate dates. 3. **Carver Bank date is \"2011\"** - just a year, not a range. If she was there 2011-2023 or 2015-2023, this needs the full range. 4. **Citigroup still says \"Community Business Group\"** - should be \"Commercial Business Group\" per our earlier edit recommendation. 5. **Governor Appointee dates now say 2010-2012** for both positions - previously it just said 2010. Having a range is better but need to confirm 2010-2012 is accurate. 6. **Jamaica YMCA date is just \"2010\"** - is that just one year or should it be a range? 7. **Bank of America entry is extremely truncated** - just one sentence with no proper formatting. Needs to be properly formatted as a full role entry. 8. **Towers Perrin bullet** - still mentions \"fellowship from the East West Center (University of Hawaii)\" - is this a fellowship? Rashida should clarify. If it was a fellowship/program, it should be listed separately in education or credentials. 9. **Page count** - still 3 pages. Goal should be 2 pages. 10. **Mixed bullet formatting** - some bullets are \"●\" and some are \"-\" which will look inconsistent. Let me organize this into a clear audit response. Key flags: - NY Life dates 2011-2013 is WRONG (should be 2006-2007) - BofA role is new and partially formed - needs proper formatting and date verification - Carver date needs full range - Citigroup division name still wrong - YMCA date needs range confirmation View Good progress — this version shows real improvements. But I caught 4 issues that need your answers before submission, including one date error that could raise red flags with HR. Here's the full audit. ✅ v4 (2) FULL AUDIT — What's Fixed, What's New, What Needs Answers ✅ WHAT YOU FIXED — CONFIRMED GOOD Fix\tStatus Executive Profile — redundant last sentence DELETED\t✅ Perfect. Now ends cleanly at \"White House Fellow.\" Jamaica YMCA Board Member — ADDED\t✅ In the right section \"Generated $40M+\" — \"Designed and\" removed\t✅ Fixed NY Life HECM bullet — rewritten as clear comms framing\t✅ Excellent — no DB/DC overreach Core Competencies — no \"Defined Benefit & DC Pension Operations\"\t✅ Correct East West Center — moved to \"fellowship\" framing\t✅ Better 🔴 STOP — 4 ISSUES REQUIRING YOUR ANSWERS BEFORE SUBMISSION 🚨 ISSUE #1 — NY Life Dates Are Wrong Detail Current in this version:\t`New York Life Investments All previous versions show:\t2006–2007 The conflict:\t2011–2013 overlaps with Ca"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=1e4a3245-344f-4222-a4d9-df5a576a2797","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=1e4a3245-344f-4222-a4d9-df5a576a2797"}]}]}]
